Here are the recent updates to http://awk.info .

(For all updates to awk.info, subscribe to
http://tinyurl.com/rss4awk. To contribute to awk.info,
see http://awk.info/?contribute .)

-----------------------------------------------------------
NEWS

Ed Morton contributes a Gawk reference card.
- http://lawker.googlecode.com/svn/fridge/share/pdf/awkcard.pdf

Panos Papadopoulos offers a new Awk Mascot (very scary)
- http://awk.info/?news/awksnake

Awk for Ethiopian multiplication
- http://awk.info/?ethiopianMultiplication

Ed Morton reveals all about WHINY_USERS
- http://awk.info/?tip/whinyUsers

TAWK= TinyAwk or a fast++ compiled Awk
- http://awk.info/?tawks
	
-----------------------------------------------------------
UPDATES

Aleksey Cheusov releases Runawk 0.17.
- http://awk.info/?news/runawk017

Jim Hart releases Awk++ (version 21)
- http://awk.info/?dsl/awkplusplus

Ted Davis generalizes his bitmap tools.
- http://awk.info/?tools/widenbmp

-----------------------------------------------------------
PAGE OF THE MONTH

Google Analytics tells us that awk.info's pages of 
the month is Jim Hart's OO-in-awk tool:

	http://awk.info/?dsl/awkplusplus

-----------------------------------------------------------
MOST AWK-ISH CITY IN THE WORLD 

The most Awk-loving city in the world is still Athens,
Greece. Residents of that city visited awk.info more
than anywhere else in the world.  

But now they've been joined by the neighboring city
Thessaloniki.

--------

Dear contributors to awk.info,

Since I'm updating the site monthly, it can take up to
4 weeks for contributions to go live.  So  keep those
cards and letters coming in and expect to see them by
the end of each month. 

Enjoy!
:-)

Tim Menzies

p.s. Awk.info wants to show to the world your great awk
code.  If you want to improve the above, or you have
other code you are particularly proud of (which you can
share), please see http://awk.info/?awk100 or
http://awk.info/?contribute
